</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497579C3C078FBC53534" blockId="12.[189,1086,311,338]" box="[189,1086,311,338]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Baltic amber is considered to be of Bartonian–Priabonian age, ca 34–38 Ma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D115497579C3C037FD503251" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497579C3C037FEB535F4" blockId="12.[189,334,376,402]" box="[189,334,376,402]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
<heading id="D0A13275D115497579C3C037FEB535F4" bold="true" box="[189,334,376,402]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD115497579C3C037FEB535F4" bold="true" box="[189,334,376,402]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11549757994C0E8FEBE35A7" blockId="12.[189,1401,423,731]" box="[234,325,423,449]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757994C0E8FEBE35A7" bold="true" box="[234,325,423,449]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497579C3C084FEE736BD" blockId="12.[189,1401,423,731]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
BODY. BL 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757847C085FEB13582" bold="true" box="[313,330,458,484]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">=</emphasis>
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD1154975782FC085FE463583" box="[337,445,458,485]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.83" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="2.83">2.83 mm</quantity>
. Head oval, subtriangular in frontal view (HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757D7FC085FB953583" box="[1025,1134,458,485]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
), bearing several short hairs, stouter on frons; eye oval, glabrous; antenna inserted on frontal shelf, at level with lower margin of eyes; toruli well separated; antenna bearing numerous short sensilla; scape shorter than head length, 5.5 times as long as wide; pedicel shorter than F1, longer than wide; 13 flagellomeres; F1 longest, two times as long as wide; F2–F13 as long as wide; F13 tapering at apex (antennomeres length of female 
<typeStatus id="54ED3BBBD115497579C1C335FED236F2" box="[191,297,634,660]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">holotype</typeStatus>
, in mm: Sc-0.44; P-0.14; F1-0.16; F2-0.10; F3-0.10; F4-0.09; F5-0.09; F6-0.09; F7-0.09; F8- 0.08; F9-0.09; F10-0.09; F11- 0.09; F12-0.09; F13-0.10); mandibles of ordinary form; occipital carina foveate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497579C3C24CFBC73050" blockId="12.[188,1401,770,1078]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
MESOSOMA. Smooth and shiny, shorter than metasoma (MsL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757AE6C24DFBFE377B" box="[920,1029,770,797]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.97">0.97 mm</quantity>
), sparsely pubescent; pronotum not elongate with distinct and uninterrupted epomia; mesoscutum distinctly convex, notauli complete and convergent; anterior scutellar pit suboval, slightly narrower than apical distance between notauli; scutellum without posterior scutellar pit; propodeum with two prominent plicae; median propodeal keel simple. Fore wing hyaline, homogeneously micropubescent, extending beyond metasoma (FwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757861C2FDFE7437AB" box="[287,399,946,973]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.71" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="2.71">2.71 mm</quantity>
); C, Sc+R, M+Cu, basal vein, marginal vein, postmarginal vein and r-rs pigmented; Cu nebulous; marginal vein length around three quarters of its distance from basal vein; marginal vein shorter than radial cell; radial cell closed by Rs; Rs pigmented distally to r-rs, inconspicuous proximally. Legs slender, with short hairs; tibial spur formula 1-2-2; tarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497579C3C511FAAD30DB" blockId="12.[189,1399,1117,1214]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
METASOMA. Petiole twice as long as wide (PtL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757A70C512FC86301E" box="[782,893,1117,1144]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.27">0.27 mm</quantity>
; PtW = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757A9AC512FBA8301E" box="[996,1107,1117,1144]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
), longitudinally striated, bearing long hairs dorsally; gaster globular, slightly longer than high (GL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757D45C5CFFB5C30FD" box="[1083,1191,1152,1179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="1.05">1.05 mm</quantity>
; GH = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757D83C5CFFA9130FD" box="[1277,1386,1152,1179]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.67">0.67 mm</quantity>
), with sparse pubescence; S2 and T2 longest; four ring-like segments discernible beyond large tergite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11549757994C5AAFED13099" blockId="12.[187,1400,1253,1491]" box="[234,298,1253,1279]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757994C5AAFED13099" bold="true" box="[234,298,1253,1279]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497579C3C446FE4431B4" blockId="12.[187,1400,1253,1491]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
BL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757877C447FE823145" box="[265,377,1288,1315]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.50 mm</quantity>
; similar to female but antennae sexually dimorphic: scape shorter than head length (HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757868C464FE7A3120" box="[278,385,1323,1350]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.53">0.53 mm</quantity>
), 5.5 times as long as wide, pedicel rounded, as long as wide, 12 flagellomeres elongate, cylindrical, longer than wide, F1 longest, with marked emargination on anterior third of segment, F2–F12 subequal in length, F12 tapering at apex (antennomeres length of male 
<typeStatus id="54ED3BBBD11549757D77C43DFB8A31EA" box="[1033,1137,1394,1420]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">paratype</typeStatus>
, in mm: Sc- 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757C7CC43DFA9431EA" box="[1282,1391,1394,1420]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.38">0.38 mm</quantity>
; P-0.11; F1-0.25; F2-0.19; F3-0.19; F4-0.19; F5-0.18; F6-0.17; F7-0.16; F8-0.16; F9-0.16; F10-0.16; F11- 0.15; F12; 0.21).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497579C3C4B6FD503251" blockId="12.[189,1399,1529,1592]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
Remaining measurements: HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757B2FC4B6FD463272" box="[593,701,1529,1556]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.3" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.53">0.53 mm</quantity>
; MsL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757A5EC4B5FC773272" box="[800,908,1530,1556]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.24" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="1.24">1.24 mm</quantity>
; FwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757A91C4B5FBA03272" box="[1007,1115,1530,1556]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.84" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="2.84">2.84 mm</quantity>
; PtL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757DCCC4B5FAE53272" box="[1202,1310,1530,1556]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.32">0.32 mm</quantity>
; PtW = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD115497579C3C752FED23251" box="[189,297,1565,1592]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
; GL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757804C752FE1D3251" box="[378,486,1565,1591]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.41" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="1.41">1.41 mm</quantity>
; GH = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11549757B45C752FD5C3251" box="[571,679,1565,1591]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" unit="mm" value="0.82">0.82 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D115497479C3C711FDBE3521" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="70" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497579C3C711FEBF321E" blockId="12.[189,324,1630,1656]" box="[189,324,1630,1656]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
<heading id="D0A13275D115497579C3C711FEBF321E" bold="true" box="[189,324,1630,1656]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD115497579C3C711FEBF321E" bold="true" box="[189,324,1630,1656]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D115497479C3C7C2FDBE3521" blockId="12.[189,1400,1676,2020]" lastBlockId="13.[189,1398,265,327]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="70" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">
Using 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11549757873C7C2FE3932C1" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[269,450,1676,1703]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
key, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11549757B78C7C2FD2032C1" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[518,731,1677,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757B78C7C2FD2032C1" box="[518,731,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Pantoclis globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11549757B9CC7C2FCC432C1" box="[738,831,1677,1703]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out to 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11549757AA7C7C2FBB332C1" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[985,1096,1677,1703]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757AA7C7C2FBB332C1" box="[985,1096,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Pantoclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: antennae inserted on a frontal prominence, mandibles not forming a beak or sickle-shaped, notauli present, scutellum without foveae along posterior margin, marginal vein nearly as long as its distance from basal vein and presence of ring-like segments beyond the large tergite, marginal vein shorter than radial cell, epomia distinct, median propodeal keel simple, petiole at most one and a third times as long as its apical width. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11549757B37C672FCE53331" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[585,798,1853,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757B37C672FCE53331" box="[585,798,1853,1879]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Pantoclis globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also fits in 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11549757AD6C672FBEC3331" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[936,1047,1853,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757AD6C672FBEC3331" box="[936,1047,1853,1879]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Pantoclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the diagnosis of Hou 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757986C62EFED7331C" box="[248,300,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">et al</emphasis>
. (2016). It differs from most extant representatives of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11549757ACAC62FFBD8331C" authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1856" box="[948,1059,1888,1914]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757ACAC62FFBD8331C" box="[948,1059,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Pantoclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the marginal vein much longer than the r-rs (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11549757B7BC6CCFD6233F8" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[517,665,1923,1950]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon 1957</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11549757BD7C6CCFCB033FB" author="Sharma S. K." box="[681,843,1923,1949]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="51 - 61" refId="ref16586" refString="Sharma S. K. 1980. On some new species of Belytinae and Diapriinae (Hymenoptera: Proctotrupoidea) from India. Oriental Insects 14 (1): 51 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1980.10434583" type="journal article" year="1980">Sharma 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11549757A24C6CCFC2633FB" author="Buhl P. N." box="[858,989,1923,1949]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="41 - 58" refId="ref14019" refString="Buhl P. N. 1998. New or little known Oriental and Australasian Belytinae (Hymenoptera: Diapriidae). Oriental Insects 32 (1): 41 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.1998.10433766" type="journal article" year="1998">Buhl 1998</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11549757A8DC6CCFF0333A6" authority="Chambers, 1974" authorityName="Chambers" authorityYear="1974" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiscapa">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757A8DC6CCFB1533FB" box="[1011,1262,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Pantoclis longiscapa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11549757D86C6CCFF0333A6" author="Chambers V. H." pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="2" refId="ref14194" refString="Chambers V. H. 1974. Taxonomic notes on the Belytinae, with a new species of Pantoclis Forster (Hym., Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae). Journal of Entomology (B) 42 (2): 127 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1974. tb 00064. x" type="journal article" year="1974">Chambers, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has a similar fore wing configuration but differs by having F1 very long and F2 distinctly longer than the following flagellomeres (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11549757B30C686FCF53382" author="Chambers V. H." box="[590,782,1993,2020]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="2" refId="ref14194" refString="Chambers V. H. 1974. Taxonomic notes on the Belytinae, with a new species of Pantoclis Forster (Hym., Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae). Journal of Entomology (B) 42 (2): 127 - 121. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1974. tb 00064. x" type="journal article" year="1974">Chambers 1974</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11549757A5AC686FB5F3385" authority="Brues, 1906" authorityName="Brues" authorityYear="1906" box="[804,1188,1993,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deperdita">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11549757A5AC686FBF13385" box="[804,1034,1993,2019]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="69">Pantoclis deperdita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11549757D6DC685FB5F3385" author="Brues C. T." box="[1043,1188,1993,2020]" pageId="12" pageNumber="69" pagination="491 - 498" refId="ref13907" refString="Brues C. T. 1906. Fossil parasitic and phytophagous Hymenoptera from Florissant, Colorado. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 22: 491 - 498. Available from http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1719 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1906">Brues, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Eocene of Florissant has a shorter radial cell and marginal vein (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11449747A1FC046FC173542" author="Brues C. T." box="[865,1004,265,292]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" pagination="491 - 498" refId="ref13907" refString="Brues C. T. 1906. Fossil parasitic and phytophagous Hymenoptera from Florissant, Colorado. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 22: 491 - 498. Available from http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1719 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1906">Brues 1906</bibRefCitation>
) and is therefore considered as a different species from 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD114497478BBC062FDC43520" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[453,575,300,326]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa">
<emphasis id="B922590BD114497478BBC062FDC43520" box="[453,575,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">P. globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
